terest in my wizzie, and I think this may be it....I'm thinking I haven't even tapped into what makes a wizard so powerful.....<br><br>-Fabidano<br>Innoruuk Wizard of the 34th Season <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uogronfionn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ogron Fionn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 6:16:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 34, Wanting To Quad (Or Learn To), Differing Opinions</span><hr size=1> Go to the library and read the post by Bicrius.<br><br>It is great.  Tells you everything you need to know.  It's how I learned how to do it.<br><br>Once you are good at quadding its highly addicting, give it a try you are sure to love it.<br><br>Suyolak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unarach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Narach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 7:30:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 34, Wanting To Quad (Or Learn To), Differing Opinions</span><hr size=1> hmm...<br><br>Where to quad at 34<br>Dire wolves in GD sounds good, if you are planniny on quading wyverns in CS (at level 51) .<br>If not, then id say cougars in IC.<br><br>Second question: SoTF - can I quad without it?<br>Yes, you can, its more difficult to master, and more difficult to learn, but can be done.<br><br>Third question (and final =)): Resists - how do I deal with them? <br>Depends how you mean deal with them - if you mean how to you stop getting resists, you cant (although the SoTF will mean lower resists), otherwise just keep going till your ooom (hopefully killing the majority of them), the zone if more are still on you. If you mean how do you deal with snare .. hmm, well what i do is a run further ahead, wait for the ensnared one(s) to get closer, then run back from where i was so that im passing the snares (this is so that i dont get too far outside agro range and they dont run off), one the unsnared ones are out of range, snare again, then circle till they are rounded up and re-snare till ALL are snared.<br><br>There is a lot of info on quading in the library as well, these are just things i have noticed while quading<br><br><br>Narach, 52 Channeler of the Red Wolf Clan<br>Zeb Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uivhon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ivhon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 8:28:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://ivhon.homestead.com/files/2rings.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 34, Wanting To Quad (Or Learn To), Differing Opinions</span><hr size=1> I found cougars to be very difficult at 34.  Pulled a few off, but had to bail as often as not.  Probably decent enough training, though.  Problem is, cougars are FAST - by the time you get BoF off, you are getting hit.  Couple this with a fairly high resist rate on BoF, and a high likelyhood of picking up a 5th (or 6th or 7th) and I found myself bailing more than finishing.  Actually gave up quadding until 37 (direwolves in IC) when I was amazed at how much easier it was.<br><br>I would say that SK would be a safer, easier place to learn (assuming its not camped all to hell).  Another option that is not mentioned (and I havent tried) is dervishes outside ToFS.  They are lower-lvl than wolves (less resists) and not as fast as cougars.  Dont know their hitpoints, tho (pretty easy to see if you have the mana, though - kite a single using CoF - if you can finish it with 20m to spare, you can quad safely).  Some people also start out doing succulents in OT (helps to have a litte VS faction).<br><br>DEFINATELY get the SoTF - it shouldnt be too hard to get at your level - might need a tank and a healer for the goblin hearts (SolA can take a while).  It is one of the best overall wizzy items in the game IMO - both in groups and for soloing.  Your nukes hit for noticeably more and you dont get hit/waste mana pulling your quads.  Great little toy.<br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>Skitzolious T. Fizzlewitz-Elentaari<br>41st Wizzy of Vazzaelle <p><p align=center><font color=red><font size=4><i>Gaidin</i> Gone Gonzo</p></font><br> "Let my inspiration flow!  Talk in rhyme, suggesting rythms..." - Grateful Dead, <i>Terrapin Station</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 9:47:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 34, Wanting To Quad (Or Learn To), Differing Opinions</span><hr size=1> if you want a good place to learn only (no XP at 34 I'm sure), go to the goblin ruins in LOIO.  There's 4 goblin warriors (green at 30, but give XP) in a building there.  Just SoW up, and run thru the building and you'll get all 4 of 'em.  You'll need to circle 'em 2 times MAX to get 'em close enough for BOF, and you can drop 'em and med to full before they respawn.  SK gnolls would give you XP, but the camping issues on them would make that REALLy tough to quad, i bet.  Also, the goblins don't run when they get low, unless they're alone.  Gnolls run no matter what. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 30th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 10:34:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 34, Wanting To Quad (Or Learn To), Differing Opinions</span><hr size=1> do what Aniar said. After you read the post in the library learn in LoiO on the gobbies. Quadding is ultra high risk - if you make a mistake it usually means you end up beat to a blood pulp at best, Loading Please Wait .... more often than not.<br><br>Once you get the hang of it I would recommend these 3 places:<br><br>1. Eastern Waste Ulthorks - start with walruses (1khp), then move to Ulthork hunters (1200hp) then finally warriors (1600hp). This will get you to 45.<br><br>2. Great Divide - Tizmaks. There is a cave full of these beasties and they are all on the same faction so they don't run when in a group. Exp should be really go and get you to 40ish.<br><br>3. Great Divide - wolves. Drakkel wolves if you plan on dorf/dragon faction (or quadding in CS later) or coldain trackers if you plan on being a giant lover. These should also get you into the low 40s.<br><br>I taught a friend of mine to quad in EW when he turned 34 - he hit 45 in under 10 days. The experience is amazing. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 58th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></span><p><b><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102 ">Moordian Kilbringer</a></b><br>Warrior of 33 Battle Scars</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 1:23:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 34, Wanting To Quad (Or Learn To), Differing Opinions</span><hr size=1> Somewhere on Graffe's site there's a &quot;manadmg.xls&quot; file that someone wrote to calculate damage possible for a certain amount of mana...  I took that and changed the spells to reflect AoE damage / MOB for a certain amount of mana.  Unfortuneately some of my spell damage values might be high (like at 34 for CoF) cause i don't know the exact damages per spell per leve, BUT it might help you figure out what you can probably kill with your mana.  Email me at ask@docsmooth.com if you're interested.  There's nothing like turning a game into a huge math problem. LOL <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 30th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dscott12>Dscott12</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/2/01 5:10:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding</span><hr size=1> Hi there,<br><br>Well, I did my first 'tri-kite' last night.  Successfully, too, I might add.  Got me 2 blue bubbles.  Did the crazed goblin camp in Butcherblock to try it out.<br><br>Thanks for the tips all, I appreciate the insight.  Something tells me this might get addictive....<br><br>-Fabi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/2/01 8:53:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding</span><hr size=1> The goblins in LOIO are the best at 29-30, IMO.  They're already bunched up for you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I found out today, however, that Splitpaw gnolls will NOT split up if you have 3 or 4 in the group.  They WILL run when they get low health if there's only 2 of them, however.  So only kite splitpaw gnolls in singles, triples, or quads. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 30th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=194.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=194.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><b